Nigeria’s Government Debt Reaches $33.4 Billion, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-10T08:36:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/nigeria-s-government-debt-reaches-33-4-billion-vanguard-says.html
Nigeria’s total debt reached $33.4
billion at the end of 2010,  Vanguard  reported, citing the
director-general of the Debt Management Office, Abraham Nwankwo.  External debt stood at $4.5 billion, while domestic
borrowing was 4.5 trillion naira ($28.9 billion), the Lagos-
based newspaper said.  The West African nation intends to limit its debt-to-gross
domestic-product-ratio to 25 percent over the next four years.
The ratio currently stands at 18 percent, Vanguard reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 